  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting households affected by the Beirut Port Explosion 2020</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The huge explosion at Beirut&#x2019;s port is a crippling blow to a country that had been reeling from a political and financial crisis, a depreciating currency and the Covid-19 pandemic. Economic damage from the blast is being estimated in the billions of dollars. The massive explosion in August 4th, 2020, that hit Beirut port and big part the city killed more than 154 people, more than 6,000 wounded and dozens of missing persons, in addition to the great material damage that affected homes of more than 300,000 thousands of families whose houses were partially or totally destroyed, who are displaced. 

The Overall Goal of the project is to support the households affected by the Beirut port explosion by providing unconditional and multi-purpose cash assistance shelter, food, and medical aid.
To achieve this goal the project intends to provide: unconditional cash assistance of an amount USD 100 per family per month for a period of two months.</narrative>
  </description>
